Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-win ners Of A Race Since November 9 Allowed 2 lbs. ; A Race Since October 9 Allowed 4 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD BERT unhurried in the early part, moved up on the outside around the turn, made a bid down the stretch and finished well. JANETS JAY JAY lacked early speed, raced outside around the turn, made a wide bid and got up for second. SAMMY DANSEUR JR. raced near the back in the beginning, made a late rail bid and was a clear third at the wire. PRIZELESS pressed the early pace, racing behind the two leaders, made a bid at the 3/8 pole and hung down the lane. BERTIE'S GALAXY dueled for the early advantage, drifted in around the turn and faded down the stretch. GRUNT vied for the early lead, saved ground around the turn, steadied, getting in tight quarters and was done. THE JOCKEY OF #4 GRUNT LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST #6 BERTIE'S GALAXY FOR INTERFERENCE AROUND THE TURN. AFTER VIEWING REPLAYS STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED #6 FROM 5TH AND PLACED HIM 6TH.
